# No New Thymeleaf (React migration track)

## When this applies

- On branches `migration/react-grind` or `migration/react-linear`, **or**
- When creating or editing files under `frontend/`.

## When this does **not** apply

- On branch `e2e-tests` when the work is **only** adding `data-testid` or small template tweaks to support Playwright **against the existing Thymeleaf UI**.
- Baseline Playwright setup and tests that target Thymeleaf.

## Rules

- Do not create **new** `.html` Thymeleaf pages for user-facing features.
- Do not add new `th:` attributes as a substitute for building UI in React.
- New user-facing UI belongs in React under `frontend/`.
- Backend changes for the SPA should expose JSON (REST), not new server-rendered HTML flows.
